<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 8:18PM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern
Wheeler, southeastern Gray and northeastern Donley Counties through
845 PM CDT...
At 818 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Mclean, or 21 miles west of Shamrock, moving north at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Mclean, Alanreed and Kellerville.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
